Purpose of this document is to define and describe the Classes which will control the information and processes at the abstract level of the system.
There shall be one class each for each thread.
Following are the description of the Classes - 
a. Camera_Manager : This Class will read the images from the Camera when the image trigger for reading is invoked. The trigger for image reading shall be invoked in two conditions-
                    I. When a customer presents an identification to the camera., and II. When the customer presents items to the camera.
b. DataBase_Manager : It will receive callbacks from the different devices, viz Camera, weighing scales, etc. and retrieve & provide the requested information from the database.
c. Display_manager : It will manage the display information on the screen.
d. Weigh_Scale_Manager : It will manage the data received from the weighing scale.
